subSubSection.paragraph:
Female genitalia. Spermatheca (
Fig. 18
) subcylindrical; collum truncate-conical, perpendicular to axis of spermathecal body, shorter than in remaining members of the species group; ramus indistinct; cornu shorter than spermathecal body, apex exceeding level of gland entrance. Spermathecal gland about 2× as long as spermatheca; spermathecal duct about 4.5× as long as spermatheca.
